relevant_communication:
In the last two decades CITEVE has taken part in more than 100 R&D projects involving more than 200 companies (Portuguese and European) among other technological partners and the focus and priorities were always the applicability of results and the acquisition of critical mass. From those 100 R&D projects, more than 20% were inside EU initiatives (FP7, H2020, LIFE, ERASMUS, SUDOE, POCTEP) 

Under the principles of collective efficiency and closer cooperation with other fields of knowledge CITEVE has always search and promote cooperation with a very diverse group of institutions. The development of CITEVE in the field of applied research and technology transfer is also strengthen by its active participation in several networks of excellence, such as: The European Technology Platform For The Future of Textiles and Clothing; Textranet - European Network of Textile Research Organizations; Fashion Competitiveness Pole; Health Cluster Portugal, Forum Manufuture, Oeko-Tex® Association, among others. 

Some exemples: 

European Projects: 
- MYWEAR (FP7 NMP): Development of a new generation of customized, eco-friendly, safe, healthy and smart work wear and sportswear products for elderly, obese, diabetics and disabled people. 
- LiVEST “uLtralIgtht weight bullet-proof VESTs” (EDA Projects ) – Development of technical and intelligent fabrics for ballistic protection; 
- ACCLITEXSYS –“ACCLImatization TEXtile SYStem” (EDA Projects ) - Different technological approaches for the stabilization of the soldier’s body temperature; 
- PIEZOTEX: Development of piezoelectric textile fibres and fabrics for sensors and energy harvesting; 
- TEMP - Textile excellence in EU-MED partners (7FP): capacity building project, towards the strengthening of the technical and scientific competence within the Euro-Mediterranean (EUROMED) region in the field of textile technology related topics. 

Publications/oral presentations/technical studies: 
- “Novel approach for integrating textiles with printed electronic circuits into automotive interior components”, 55th Man-Made Fibers Congress, Dornbirn – Austria (21.9.2016); 
- PIEZOTEX project - Fibres with piezolectric properties”, iTechstyle Fórum – Modtissimo Porto (26.09.2013) (shared with Swerea IVF); 
- Technical textiles studies “–Mobility and Transports (2011) and Habitat (2015)" 

Patents: 
- Polymeric multi-layered injection-moulded article with an electric circuit, production method thereof - Simoldes Plásticos, CeNTI and CITEVE (EP 3 065 516 A1 (9/09/2016)) 
- A textile multi-layered injection-moulded article comprising printed electronic circuits, manufactured process and uses thereof - Simoldes Plásticos, CeNTI and CITEVE (28/09/2016)
